## 4. Realtime SSE

SSE handlers live under `src/app/api/realtime/<feature>/[<id>/]route.ts`
and use `createSseStream` from `@/server/realtime/sse` for the wire shape.
The bus is regular Redis (`REDIS_URL`, ioredis), not Upstash — Upstash REST
doesn't support pub/sub.

```typescript
// src/app/api/realtime/<feature>/[id]/route.ts
import { requireAuth } from '@/server/api/auth';
import { createSseStream } from '@/server/realtime/sse';

export const runtime = 'nodejs';
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic';

export async function GET(req: Request, { params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }) {
  const auth = await requireAuth(req);
  if (!auth.ok) return auth.response;
  const { id } = await params;

  // Authorize the resource before subscribing
  await assertOwnership(auth.user.uid, id);

  return createSseStream({
    channels: [`feature:${id}`],
    signal: req.signal,
    onConnect: async () => JSON.stringify(await loadInitialSnapshot(id)),
    onMessage: (_channel, message) => message, // forward verbatim, or filter
  });
}
```

**Required:**

- [ ] Auth at the route boundary (`requireAuth` or page-level equivalent)
- [ ] Authorize the specific resource before subscribing — channel names
      are predictable; never trust them
- [ ] Pass `req.signal` to `createSseStream` so client-disconnect tears
      down the Redis subscription
- [ ] `runtime = 'nodejs'` and `dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`
- [ ] Producers publish via `redis.publish(channel, JSON.stringify(...))`
      from server handlers / queue consumers, never from the route file

**Forbidden:**

- ❌ Edge runtime (ioredis won't work)
- ❌ Custom heartbeat logic — `createSseStream` already sends `: hb\n\n`
- ❌ Unbounded `onMessage` handlers that allocate per-message — keep them
     pure and tight

---

## Quick reference

| Family | Auth helper | Idempotency | Body shape | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Queues | (none — invoked privately by Vercel) | `withIdempotency` mandatory | `handleCallback` parses | `runtime = 'nodejs'` |
| Cron | `requireCronAuth` | optional, on per-day key if needed | typically empty `GET` | `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>` |
| Webhooks | provider signature / token | `withIdempotency` by external event id | `req.text()` for Stripe | Always 200 on accept |
| SSE | `requireAuth` + resource check | n/a | streaming `Response` | `req.signal` + ioredis |

For the broader pattern selection, see `architecture-decision-rules.mdc`.
